cat_summary: 2ish year old white and tabby lady
cat_timing: Ready now, fosterer can meet you at the cafe
cat_description: Buffy was found in a basement along with her 3 kittens, Willow, Xander and Oz. They were hungry, dirty, and covered in fleas, yet not scared of us. Apparently Buffy was once owned and then left behind, which would explain how social she is. She is extremely friendly and happy to have been rescued. She walked into the carrier without a problem.She's been doing well in foster - lots of energy and adores playing! She even plays fetch. From her foster: Buffy is a friendly tabby who enjoys exploring as well as taking long naps. She loves playing with toys, particularly wands and anything else with a string. She is comfortable with being picked up, but doesn’t like being held too long. She likes to roam around the home exploring every corner and climbing onto high places (think top of the refrigerator). Buffy is fond of treats, all shapes and sizes, as well as eating her meals on time and she’ll let you know if she’s hungry with some chirps. She seems pretty active and will likely do well in a home where she can get plenty of attention and may enjoy having a feline friend. She would most likely do best in a home without children as she can still be a bit skittish and nip when scared, but she is making great progress and is a total delight.Please note, Buffy has a lot of energy and can play rough! We'll help you prepare a plan to keep her occupied and on the right track but she'll need some dedication.** Select Foster Pick Up (cafe) when scheduling****

cat_timing: Needs a home ASAP
cat_description: From her fosterer: Castle is the sweetest friend to have around the house. She might be a little slow to warm up to you at first, but once you have won her loyalty, this tabby won’t be afraid to follow you around, nudge, and nuzzle you. She will greet you at the door when you come home each day and will meow when she’s hungry or when she wants you to wake up and give her attention. She goes absolutely crazy for chicken treats and will climb onto your lap for one. Castle is independent, explorative, and confident, and a sweet household companion who takes great interest in all that her humans do. She does have some kidney issues, which are currently stable but requires a special food – which, luckily, she loves. ** Select Foster Pick Up (Cafe) when scheduling****

cat_timing: Ready now, at the cafe
cat_description: China was returned to us after over a year by an owner who said he was being rough with her, attacking her feet. He's been lovely with us and did well in foster prior to his adoption. That said, he should likely go to a home with a foster that is comfortable putting him on a strict play schedule to redirect his energy (3 meals a day each preceded by a wand toy session) and dealing with any potential rough play with calm and boundries. He's really a beautiful cat and really loving.  China's former foster wants to adopt him but needs a month to get ready. Can you give him a place to crash till then?

cat_timing: Ready now, rescuer can meet you at the cafe
cat_description: From her rescuer: Dahlia was found wandering around in Sunset Park in early April. She is extremely friendly, and was very clearly a pet at one time. We noticed she had a spay tattoo and we had her scanned for a chip. Her chip was unregistered unfortunately, and we attempted to reach her owners via social media and other channels, but no one stepped forward. This cat is the perfect solo cat: independent, easy going, playful, affectionate and eats well. She seeks pets and love from humans, but hates other cats and definitely needs to be the only one in the house. She loves string toys, catnip toys, bird watching, and has perfect litter box manners. Please pick pick up (cafe) when scheduling.

cat_timing: Need a home by May 5th
cat_description: From their current fosterer: These one-year-old playful balls of energy will have you laughing at their antics and will definitely make their presence felt in your home. They love to play, whether it’s chasing each other madly around during their morning and evening zoomies, or pouncing on each other during their daily wrestling matches. Like all young cats, they are fond of toys, boxes, and any small object they can bat around and play with. They enjoy spending time looking out the window, surveilling everything happening outside. (Watch out plants, they might like to use you as toys too!)Dipsy (black and white boy) is the braver, more inquisitive and more confident of the pair.. He loves snuggles, whether it’s being your big or little spoon, and regularly seeks out affection during the day. He trills to get your attention and frequently asks for pets. He’ll follow you from room to room, making sure you’re still there, and will often come when called.Tinky Winky (tabby girl) is the shyer of the pair and likes her space. She likes to interact on her own terms, and while not fond of pets, she does enjoy interacting with feet through the bed covers.They both love food and will come running as soon as they hear the crack of the food can or the rustle of the dry food bag. They’re wild about Churus - Dipsy, in particular, can sniff out a freshly opened packed from the other side of the apartment and will rush to get some into his belly immediately! Tinky Winky loves Churus too, although is more reserved about asking for it.These sweet young cats would do well with a single adopter or a work from home couple, who will give them the time and patience they need to feel comfortable around new people and the confidence to open up in their own way.
full_html:
Dipsy and Tinky Winky

1 year-old brother and sister

Need a home by May 5th

From their current fosterer: These one-year-old playful balls of energy will have you laughing at their antics and will definitely make their presence felt in your home. They love to play, whether it’s chasing each other madly around during their morning and evening zoomies, or pouncing on each other during their daily wrestling matches. Like all young cats, they are fond of toys, boxes, and any small object they can bat around and play with. They enjoy spending time looking out the window, surveilling everything happening outside. (Watch out plants, they might like to use you as toys too!)

Dipsy (black and white boy) is the braver, more inquisitive and more confident of the pair.. He loves snuggles, whether it’s being your big or little spoon, and regularly seeks out affection during the day. He trills to get your attention and frequently asks for pets. He’ll follow you from room to room, making sure you’re still there, and will often come when called.

Tinky Winky (tabby girl) is the shyer of the pair and likes her space. She likes to interact on her own terms, and while not fond of pets, she does enjoy interacting with feet through the bed covers.

They both love food and will come running as soon as they hear the crack of the food can or the rustle of the dry food bag. They’re wild about Churus - Dipsy, in particular, can sniff out a freshly opened packed from the other side of the apartment and will rush to get some into his belly immediately! Tinky Winky loves Churus too, although is more reserved about asking for it.

These sweet young cats would do well with a single adopter or a work from home couple, who will give them the time and patience they need to feel comfortable around new people and the confidence to open up in their own way.

cat_description: Poor Earl was recently adopted from the city shelter only to be dumped on the adopters friend days later when it it was "too hard" to introduce him to a dog. Help him get set up permanently for the good life! It sounds like he would love an active home that could give him lots of play time and lap time. He will run up to you and wrap his paws around your leg to let you know that he wants to cuddle. He insists on sitting on his humans lap, when he is done he will climb up on your shoulder and use it as a launching pad to his favorite perching spot. So adorable!Please choose "intake" type pick up appointment

cat_timing: Needs a home by 5/4
cat_description: Elmo is a gentle, playful boy just waiting to blossom! He never tires of chasing wand toys and ball toys, sometimes launching himself onto the scratching post in hot pursuit. Elmo has not met a toy he doesn’t like! When he’s feeling safe around you, he loves scritches and turns into an absolute purring machine. He is currently afraid of strangers and sudden actions, and needs to be in a patient home where his boundaries are respected. He will also thrive in a home where he gets a lot of active play time. With the right support, Elmo warms up quickly and wants to follow you around, protect you while you’re using the toilet, and help you with your chores by chasing the Swiffer. He also has the cutest little chirps.

cat_timing: Ready now, can meet you at the cafe
cat_description: This sweet friend appeared near a feeding station and asked for assistance! A feeder easily put her in a carrier. She surprised us a few days later with a single, adorable, kitten and soon agreed to take on 5(!!!) more. Mom of the year! Ro is a wonderful mother and very dedicated to her brood, keeping them ship-shape, and snacks. She's adoring of her human friends as well, but does not seem to like other cats. The kittens are all beginning to eat solid food so we're ready for them to head off to a foster family for a few weeks until they are ready for adoption in pairs. You may have to supplement a bit with syringe feeding for a few days until they totally get the hang of the solid stuff! Please note we'll need Mama back for the day in a few weeks to get her spayed!

cat_summary: 5 year old tabby and white female
cat_timing: Ready now, can meet you at the cafe
cat_description: Peaches is being rehomed due to allergies. Please pick "intake" type pick up appointment. From her person: Peaches is a tender 5 year old lady who loves to lounge and keep watch out the window. She is shy with new folks at first but will soon be circling your legs once gentle introductions have been made. Peaches has a voracious appetite and loves to hunt - she’s caught roaches, flys, spiders, and mice! After getting over a sensitive stomach as a young kitten, Peaches has never had any health concerns other than trying not to eat too much.  Peaches can be skittish around sudden movements and would do best in a home with humans who are familiar with the ways of cats. But once she’s comfortable with you, Peaches loves to curl up next to you on the couch. Rumor has it she has the softest belly in town, so get ready to give her velvety tummy a good rub!

cat_description: From his rescuer: Pebble is a former deli cat who was fed occasionally and relatively uncared for and unwanted at his former “home.” When two of our volunteers were out trapping they happened upon him and his "owners" insisted he be taken away as well.On to a safer and brighter life, Pebble!This snowy white fella seems to be about 7 years old, and he is really coming around at his foster and is relaxing more every day. He can be a bit tense, but with a patient human (and NO cats, please!) he warms up to a bed chilling silly sweet guy. He loves loves loves toys, or any item he can turn into a game! He is obsessed with chopsticks and loves skittering them on the floor and carrying them proudly in his mouth like a stick. He also loves giving leg rubs, enjoys pets when he is relaxed and is showing signs of wanting to cuddle more. ***please pick (intake) option when scheduling pick up!

cat_timing: Ready now, rescuer can meet you at the cafe
cat_description: From her rescuer: Lola was rescued outside a deli store at 3:30am, she was meowing her heart out and followed a local colony care taker who called her to offer her food. She was not interested in food at all and started to rub herself against the ground and legs of the caretaker. Lola seemed clean, well groomed, extremely friendly with some Abyssinian cat patterns on her fur. Flyers were posted around the block where she was found. She was also posted on lost and found websites. However, nobody claimed her. It was also believed that she belonged to the deli-store but they denied ownership. While waiting for her rightful owner to appear, Lola was fully vetted and microchipped.She is currently being held at the rescuer’s home and she has demonstrated to be very needy of human contact, very chatty, and interested toy-rattle mice. However, she is not doing so great with the rescuers’ resident cats. Maybe Lola needs a very slow introduction to new cats but she tends to growl, hiss and spike up when she sees another cat, even though the other cat has not even noticed her presence.  Rescuer believes she would do better as a solo cat.Lola is litter box trained, she can be held in arms.

cat_description: From their person, who sadly has to surrender them due to allergies: Omega and Zeta are by far the cutest bonded pair ever. They are super playful, energetic, and so sweet. They respond to their names (Omega and Zeta), and they also love to cuddle. Omega and Zeta will play with anything they find on the floor, from a paper ball to anything that makes a crunching sound. They love to be petted and purr very loudly. They are super affectionate and get along well with others (humans and even some cats). They are indeed lap cats. If Omega and Zeta find you sitting, they will both try to sit on your lap. If they aren’t sitting on your lap, they are following you around the house and sitting near you. They are very independent cats, but they also love attention. They love gazing out the windows too. Fun fact about Zeta, he loves water and loves to play with it as well. Zeta and Omega

1 year old siblings

Ready now, can meet you at the cafe

From their person, who sadly has to surrender them due to allergies: Omega and Zeta are by far the cutest bonded pair ever. They are super playful, energetic, and so sweet. They respond to their names (Omega and Zeta), and they also love to cuddle. Omega and Zeta will play with anything they find on the floor, from a paper ball to anything that makes a crunching sound. They love to be petted and purr very loudly. They are super affectionate and get along well with others (humans and even some cats). They are indeed lap cats. If Omega and Zeta find you sitting, they will both try to sit on your lap. If they aren’t sitting on your lap, they are following you around the house and sitting near you. They are very independent cats, but they also love attention. They love gazing out the windows too. Fun fact about Zeta, he loves water and loves to play with it as well. They do not scratch or bite people, either. But they will give you little head rubs.
